@{
    // Titles + meta are set in ToolsController
}

<style>
    .count-page h1 { display: none; }
</style>

<div class="mx-auto" style="max-width: 1100px;">
    <h1 class="mb-2">Character counter</h1>
    <p class="text-muted mb-3">
        Count characters, words, and lines instantly. Use presets for Tweet/X and common SEO metadata length guidance.
    </p>

    @await Html.PartialAsync("_CharCountWidget", "Character count")

    <hr class="my-4" />

    <h2 class="h5">Use cases</h2>
    <p class="text-muted">
        Perfect for staying within UI limits (buttons, labels, form fields), social posts, and SEO snippets. The presets provide practical guidance,
        but different platforms can count characters differently — treat them as best-effort.
    </p>

    <h2 class="h5 mt-4">How to use</h2>
    <ol class="text-muted">
        <li>Paste your text.</li>
        <li>Optionally select a preset (Tweet/X, meta title, meta description).</li>
        <li>Watch the counts update live — and the preset feedback color (green/yellow/red).</li>
    </ol>

    <h2 class="h5">FAQs</h2>
    <div class="d-grid gap-2">
        <details>
            <summary class="fw-semibold">Which count does SEO usually care about?</summary>
            <div class="text-muted mt-2">Typically character counts including spaces. The presets in this tool use that measure.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary class="fw-semibold">Why is there a “chars (no spaces)” stat?</summary>
            <div class="text-muted mt-2">It’s helpful when you’re counting identifiers, codes, or compact strings where whitespace isn’t meaningful.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary class="fw-semibold">Are the SEO limits exact?</summary>
            <div class="text-muted mt-2">They’re typical ranges, not strict rules. Search results often truncate by pixels/device, not a fixed character count.</div>
        </details>
        <details>
            <summary class="fw-semibold">Need to clean or inspect structured text?</summary>
            <div class="text-muted mt-2">Try the <a href="/json-viewer">JSON viewer</a> for payloads or <a href="/text-compare">Text compare</a> for diffs.</div>
        </details>
    </div>
</div>

